Legendary rock band KISS will be performing in Johannesburg in July 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Legendary rock band KISS is heading to South Africa to perform for one-night-only in Johannesburg in July 2020. Tickets for the End of the Road tour are available from Big Concert's website. WATCH: Local artists object to Burna Boy performing in SA KISS will perform in South Africa on 25 July 2020 at the Ticketpro Dome in Johannesburg. The band, which has sold more than 100 million albums worldwide, was formed by Paul Stanley, Gene Simmons, Peter Criss, and Ace Frehley in New York City in 1973. They are known for their songs like Rock and Roll All Nite, Cold Gin, War Machine and Morden Day Delilah.